methods.name: createSectionProviderFor
methods.comment:
Iterates through the statically registered #sectionProviderFactoryFuncs,
 trying each factory method until one returns a DWARFSectionProvider 
 that can successfully retrieve the DWARFSectionNames#MINIMAL_DWARF_SECTIONS 
 sections we need to do a DWARF import.
 
 The resulting DWARFSectionProvider is Closeable and it is the caller's
 responsibility to ensure that the object is closed when done.

return.comment:
DWARFSectionProvider that should be closed by the caller or NULL if no
 section provider types match the specified program.

name: DWARFSectionProviderFactory
comment: Auto-detects which DWARFSectionProvider matches a Ghidra program.

fields.javadoc:
A list of references to static methods that will create a {@link DWARFSectionProvider}.

The method should return null if it can't parse the data it found in the {@link Program}.

The method does NOT need to worry about validating the presence of DWARF debug info sections, as that will be done in {@link #createSectionProviderFor(Program)}.

The method should not throw anything, instead just return a NULL.
fields.name: sectionProviderFactoryFuncs
fields.comment:
A list of references to static methods that will create a DWARFSectionProvider.
 
 The method should return null if it can't parse the data it found in the Program.
 
 The method does NOT need to worry about validating the presence of DWARF debug info
 sections, as that will be done in #createSectionProviderFor(Program).
 
 The method should not throw anything, instead just return a NULL.
